    detailedExplanationExpert: "Logical Fallacies - Informal Logic - This is a textbook trinitarian circulus in probando: P (God exists) → Q (Bible is true) → R (Bible is God's word) → P. The inferential circle is complete with no external anchor. Each proposition derives its warrant exclusively from the others, making the entire system epistemically closed and unfalsifiable.",
    questionFormat: "standard"
